<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">
possible. If an Award is subject to the requirements of Internal Revenue Code Section&nbsp;409A, to the extent that the Company or an Affiliate takes any action that causes a violation of
Internal Revenue Code Section&nbsp;409A or fails to take reasonable actions required to comply with Internal Revenue Code Section&nbsp;409A, in each case as determined by the Committee, the Company shall pay an additional amount to the Participant
(or beneficiary) equal to the additional income tax imposed pursuant to Internal Revenue Code Section&nbsp;409A on the Participant as a result of such violation, plus any taxes imposed on this additional payment. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B>Recommendation and Required Affirmative Vote </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">The Board of Directors unanimously recommends that shareholders vote <B>FOR </B>the approval of the proposed amendment to the Apache 2011 Omnibus Equity Compensation Plan to increase the number of shares
of the Company&#146;s common stock authorized for issuance under the plan. Because each of Apache&#146;s directors and executive officers will be eligible to receive Awards under the proposed amendment to the 2011 Plan, each of the directors and
executive officers of Apache has an interest in, and may benefit from, the adoption of the proposed amendment. The affirmative vote of the holders of a majority of the shares of the Company&#146;s common stock voted, in person or by proxy, and
entitled to vote at the 2013 annual meeting is required to approve the amendment to the 2011 Plan. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B>Consequences of Non-Approval
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">The Company considers shareholder approval of the amendment to the 2011 Plan to be critical to the Company&#146;s ability to retain and
attract employees, officers, and directors whose services are necessary to carry out the Company&#146;s business plan. If the shareholders do not approve the proposed amendment to the 2011 Plan, the Company believes its ability to retain and attract
talented personnel will be adversely affected due to the ability of the competitors of the Company to offer long-term equity compensation to talented individuals under equity plans already in place. Additionally, we would have to consider providing
additional cash compensation to our key employees to maintain competitive levels of compensation. However, our ability to align the compensation provided to our employees and officers with the interests of shareholders would be impaired. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B>THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS UNANIMOUSLY RECOMMENDS THAT YOU VOTE &#147;FOR&#148; APPROVAL OF THE PROPOSED AMENDMENT TO THE 2011 OMNIBUS EQUITY COMPENSATION
PLAN TO INCREASE THE NUMBER OF SHARES OF THE COMPANY&#146;S COMMON STOCK AUTHORIZED FOR ISSUANCE UNDER THE PLAN. </B></FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">81 </FONT></P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B><A NAME="toc470199_36"></A>APPROVAL OF AN AMENDMENT TO </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B>APACHE&#146;S RESTATED CERTIFICATE OF INCORPORATION </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B>TO ELIMINATE THE CLASSIFIED BOARD OF DIRECTORS </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B>TO PROVIDE FOR THE ANNUAL
ELECTION OF ALL DIRECTORS </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B>(ITEM NO. 7 ON PROXY CARD) </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">Apache&#146;s Amended and Restated Certificate of Incorporation (the &#147;Restated Certificate of Incorporation&#148;) currently provides that the Board of Directors be divided so that as nearly
numerically possible one-third of the directors are elected at each annual meeting of shareholders to serve a three year term. </FONT></P>  <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">In response
to a vote by shareholders at our 2012 annual meeting of shareholders on a non-binding shareholder proposal to eliminate the classification of the Board of Directors and provide for the election of all directors annually, the Corporate Governance and
Nominating (&#147;CG&amp;N&#148;) Committee, as well as the Board of Directors, considered carefully the advantages and disadvantages of maintaining a classified board structure. </FONT></P>  <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">The Board recognizes that the shareholders expressed a preference for the declassification of the Board at the 2012 annual meeting. In determining whether to support the repeal of our classified Board of
Directors, the Board considered the arguments in favor of and against continuation of the classified Board structure and determined that, given the results of the shareholders&#146; vote at the 2012 annual meeting, a majority of our shareholders
believe it would be in the best interest of Apache and its shareholders to declassify the Board of Directors. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">Therefore, the Board of
Directors has determined, in view of the shareholders&#146; vote at the 2012 annual meeting, to unanimously adopt an amendment to Article NINTH of the Company&#146;s Restated Certificate of Incorporation to eliminate the classification of the Board
of Directors over a three-year period and to submit the amendment to the shareholders of the Company. The text of the proposed amendment to Article NINTH of the Restated Certificate of Incorporation is attached to this proxy statement as
<U>Annex&nbsp;C</U>. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">The affirmative vote of shareholders holding at least four-fifths (80%)&nbsp;of the Company&#146;s issued and outstanding
common stock is required to approve the proposed amendment. If the shareholders approve the proposed amendment, then, beginning at the 2014 annual meeting, directors standing for election will be elected to one-year terms. The existing terms of
directors elected prior to or at the 2013 annual meeting will not be shortened. The entire Board of Directors will be elected annually beginning at the 2016 annual meeting. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">If approved by the shareholders, the proposed amendment to the Restated Certificate of Incorporation will become effective upon the filing of Articles of Amendment to the Restated Certificate of
Incorporation with the Secretary of State of Delaware. If the shareholders do not approve the proposed amendment, then the Board of Directors will remain classified, and all directors will continue to be elected to three-year terms. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B>IN LIGHT OF THE SHAREHOLDERS&#146; VOTE AT THE 2012 ANNUAL MEETING, THE BOARD UNANIMOUSLY RECOMMENDS A VOTE &#147;FOR&#148; THE PROPOSED AMENDMENT TO
THE COMPANY&#146;S RESTATED CERTIFICATE OF INCORPORATION TO ELIMINATE THE CLASSIFIED BOARD OF DIRECTORS TO PROVIDE FOR THE ANNUAL ELECTION OF ALL DIRECTORS. </B></FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">82 </FONT></P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B><A NAME="toc470199_37"></A>FUTURE SHAREHOLDER PROPOSALS AND DIRECTOR NOMINATIONS
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">Shareholders are entitled to submit proposals on matters appropriate for shareholder action consistent with regulations of the SEC and the
Company&#146;s bylaws. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">In order for such proposal to be properly brought before next year&#146;s annual meeting, written notice of the
proposal that complies with the Company&#146;s bylaws must be received by the Company&#146;s corporate secretary (at the address below) not less than 120 days prior to the meeting, which is expected to be held in May 2014. Nominations of persons for
election to the Board of Directors at the 2014 annual meeting likewise must be given in writing, comply with the Company&#146;s bylaws, and be received by the Company&#146;s corporate secretary not less than 120 days prior to the meeting, which is
expected to be held in May 2014. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">In addition to the foregoing, should a shareholder wish to have a proposal appear in the Company&#146;s proxy
statement for next year&#146;s annual meeting, under the regulations of the SEC, such proposal must be received by the Company&#146;s corporate secretary at 2000 Post Oak Boulevard, Suite 100, Houston, Texas 77056-4400 on or before December&nbsp;5,
2013. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B><A NAME="toc470199_38"></A>SHAREHOLDERS WITH THE SAME LAST NAME AND ADDRESS </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">The SEC rules permit companies and intermediaries (such as brokers) to implement a delivery procedure known as &#147;householding.&#148; Under this
procedure, multiple Apache shareholders who reside at the same address may receive a single set of proxy materials, unless one or more of the shareholders has provided contrary instructions. This procedure reduces printing costs and postage fees and
saves natural resources. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">If you hold your shares in &#147;street name&#148; (your shares are held in a brokerage account or by a bank or other
nominee), you may revoke your consent to householding at any time by writing to Broadridge, Householding Department, 51 Mercedes Way, Edgewood, New York 11717. You can also request information about householding from your broker or bank. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">If you are a shareholder of record (your shares are held in your own name and not held in a brokerage account) who received a household mailing this year,
and you would like to have additional copies of proxy materials mailed to you or if you would like to opt out of householding for future mailings, please send your written request to Wells Fargo Bank, N.A., Shareowner Services, Attn:
Householding/Apache Corporation, P. O. Box 64854, St. Paul, MN 55164-0854, or call (651)&nbsp;450-4104. </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">83 </FONT></P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">Solicitation of proxies for use at the annual meeting may be made in person or by mail or telephone, by directors, officers and regular employees of the
Company. These persons will receive no special compensation for any solicitation activities. The Company has requested banking institutions, brokerage firms, custodians, trustees, nominees and fiduciaries to forward solicitation materials to the
beneficial owners of shares of the Company&#146;s common stock for whom they are record holder, and the Company will, upon request, reimburse reasonable forwarding expenses. The Company has retained Georgeson Inc. to assist in soliciting proxies
from brokers, bank nominees, and other institutional holders for a fee not to exceed $13,500 plus expenses. All costs of the solicitation will be borne by the Company. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:54%"><FONT

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B><A NAME="toc470199_40"></A>Annex A </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B>AMENDMENT TO </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B>THE </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B>APACHE CORPORATION 2011 OMNIBUS EQUITY COMPENSATION PLAN </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B>Effective May&nbsp;16, 2013 </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B><U>WITNESSETH</U>: </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:10%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B>WHEREAS</B>, Apache Corporation, a Delaware corporation (the &#147;Company&#148;), established and maintains the Apache Corporation
2011 Omnibus Equity Compensation Plan (the &#147;Plan&#148;), as it may be amended and restated from time to time; and </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:10%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B>WHEREAS</B>, the Plan was approved by the Company&#146;s shareholders on May&nbsp;5, 2011; and </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:10%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B>WHEREAS</B>, Section&nbsp;4.1 of the Plan provides for the number of shares of $0.625 par value common stock of the Company (the
&#147;Shares&#148;) which are authorized for issuance under the Plan; and </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:10%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B>WHEREAS</B>, pursuant to Section&nbsp;16 of the
Plan, the Board of Directors of the Company (the &#147;Board&#148;) may, from time to time, amend or modify the Plan, subject to approval by the Company&#146;s shareholders as required; and </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:10%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B>WHEREAS</B>, the Board desires to amend the Plan to increase the number of Shares authorized for issuance under the Plan by adding
17,000,000 shares to the 25,500,000 Shares currently authorized under the Plan. </FONT></P>  <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:10%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B>NOW THEREFORE</B>, the Plan is hereby
amended as follows: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">1. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:10%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">Effective May&nbsp;16, 2013<B>, </B>Section&nbsp;4.1 of the Plan is hereby amended to read in its entirety as follows: </FONT></P>  <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">&#147;4.1 <U>Number of Shares</U>. Subject to adjustments pursuant to Section&nbsp;4.4 hereof, up to (a)&nbsp;25,500,000 shares of Stock are authorized for issuance under the Plan plus (b)&nbsp;effective
May&nbsp;16, 2013, 17,000,000 additional shares of Stock are authorized for issuance under the Plan in accordance with the Plan&#146;s terms and subject to such restrictions or other provisions as the Committee may from time to time deem necessary.
Notwithstanding the foregoing, the number of aggregate shares of Stock available for issuance under the Plan at any given time shall be reduced by (i)&nbsp;1.0 share for each share of Stock delivered in settlement of any Stock Option or Stock
Appreciation Right or Dividend Equivalent related to a Stock Appreciation Right, and (ii)&nbsp;2.39 shares for each share of Stock delivered in settlement of any Award that is not a Stock Option or Stock Appreciation Right or Dividend Equivalent
related to a Stock Appreciation Right. During the duration of the Plan, no Eligible Person may be granted Options which in the aggregate cover in excess of 5 percent of the total shares of Stock authorized under the Plan. No Award may be granted
under the Plan on or after the 10-year anniversary of the Effective Date. The foregoing to the contrary notwithstanding, within the aggregate limit described in the first sentence of this Section&nbsp;4.1, up to 25,500,000 (effective May&nbsp;16,
2013, up to 42,500,000) shares of Stock may be issued pursuant to ISOs granted under the Plan.&#148; </FONT></P>  <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">2. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:10%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">Except as specifically set forth above, the terms of the Plan shall continue in full force and effect. </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">A-1
</FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">A-2
</FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B><A NAME="toc470199_41"></A>Annex B </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B>APACHE CORPORATION </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B>2011 OMNIBUS EQUITY COMPENSATION PLAN </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">Section&nbsp;1 </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">Introduction </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">1.1
<I><U>Establishment.</U></I> Apache Corporation, a Delaware corporation (hereinafter referred to, together with its Affiliates (as defined below) as the &#147;Company&#148; except where the context otherwise requires), hereby establishes the Apache
Corporation 2011 Omnibus Equity Compensation Plan (the &#147;Plan&#148;), as it may be amended and restated from time to time. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">1.2
<I><U>Purpose</U>.</I> The purpose of the Plan is to provide Eligible Persons designated by the Committee for participation in the Plan with equity-based incentives to: (i)&nbsp;encourage such individuals to continue in the long-term service of the
Company and its Affiliates, (ii)&nbsp;create in such individuals a more direct interest in the future success of the operations of the Company, (iii)&nbsp;attract outstanding individuals, and (iv)&nbsp;retain and motivate such individuals. The Plan
is intended to provide eligible individuals with the opportunity to invest in the Company, thereby relating incentive compensation to increases in stockholder value and more closely aligning the compensation of such individuals with the interests of
the Company&#146;s stockholders. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">Accordingly, this Plan provides for the granting of Incentive Stock Options, Non-Qualified Stock Options,
Performance Awards, Restricted Stock, Restricted Stock Units, Stock Appreciation Rights or any combination of the foregoing, as the Committee determines is best suited to the circumstances of the particular individual as provided herein. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">1.3 <I><U>Effective Date</U>.</I> The Effective Date of the Plan (the &#147;Effective Date&#148;) is May&nbsp;5, 2011. This Plan and each Award granted
hereunder are conditioned on and shall be of no force or effect until the Plan is approved by the stockholders of the Company. The Committee (or its delegate in accordance with Section&nbsp;3.4(b) hereof) may award grants, the entitlement to which
shall be expressly subject to the condition that the Plan shall have been approved by the stockholders of the Company. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">Section&nbsp;2 </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">Definitions </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">2.1
<I><U>Definitions</U></I>. The following terms shall have the meanings set forth below: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">(a)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><I><U>&#147;Administrative Agent&#148;</U></I> means any designee or agent that may be appointed by the Committee pursuant to subsections 3.1(h) and 3.4 hereof.
</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><I><U>&#147;Affiliate&#148;</U></I> means any entity other than the Company that is affiliated with the Company through stock or equity ownership or
otherwise and is designated as an Affiliate for purposes of the Plan by the Committee; <U>provided</U>, <U>however</U>, that, notwithstanding any other provisions of the Plan to the contrary, for purposes of NQSOs and SARs, if an individual who
otherwise qualifies as an Eligible Person provides services to such an entity and not to the Company, such entity may only be </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>

designated an Affiliate if the Company qualifies as a &#147;service recipient,&#148; within the meaning of Internal Revenue Code Section&nbsp;409A, with respect to such individual;
<U>provided</U> <U>further</U> that such definition of &#147;service recipient&#148; shall be determined by (a)&nbsp;applying Internal Revenue Code Section&nbsp;1563(a)(1), (2), and (3), for purposes of determining a controlled group of corporations
under Internal Revenue Code Section&nbsp;414(b), using the language &#147;at least 50 percent&#148; instead of &#147;at least 80 percent&#148; each place it appears in Internal Revenue Code Section&nbsp;1563(a)(1), (2), and (3), and by applying
Treasury Regulations Section&nbsp;1.414(c)-2, for purposes of determining trades or businesses (whether or not incorporated) that are under common control for purposes of Internal Revenue Code Section&nbsp;414(c), using the language &#147;at least
50 percent&#148; instead of &#147;at least 80 percent&#148; each place it appears in Treasury Regulations Section&nbsp;1.414(c)-2, and (b)&nbsp;where the use of Shares with respect to the grant of an Option or SAR to such an individual is based upon
legitimate business criteria, by applying Internal Revenue Code Section&nbsp;1563(a)(1), (2), and (3), for purposes of determining a controlled group of corporations under Internal Revenue Code Section&nbsp;414(b), using the language &#147;at least
20 percent&#148; instead of &#147;at least 80 percent&#148; at each place it appears in Internal Revenue Code Section&nbsp;1563(a)(1), (2), and (3), and by applying Treasury Regulations Section&nbsp;1.414(c)-2, for purposes of determining trades or
businesses (whether or not incorporated) that are under common control for purposes of Internal Revenue Code Section&nbsp;414(c), using the language &#147;at least 20 percent&#148; instead of &#147;at least 80 percent&#148; at each place it appears
in Treasury Regulations Section&nbsp;1.414(c)-2; provided further that for purposes of ISOs, &#147;Affiliate&#148; shall mean any present or future corporation which is or would be a &#147;subsidiary corporation&#148; of the Company as the term is
defined in Section&nbsp;424(f) of the Internal Revenue Code. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">(l)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><I><U>&#147;Fair Market Value&#148;</U></I> means the per share closing price of the Stock as reported on The New York Stock Exchange, Inc. Composite Transactions
Reporting System for a particular date or, if the Stock is not so listed on such date, as reported on NASDAQ or on such other exchange or electronic trading system which, on the date in question, reports the largest number of traded shares of Stock,
<U>provided</U>, <U>however</U>, that if on the date Fair Market Value is to be determined there are no transactions in the Stock, Fair Market Value shall be determined as of the immediately preceding date on which there were transactions in the
Stock; <U>provided</U> <U>further</U>, <U>however</U>, that if the foregoing provisions are not applicable, the fair market value of a share of the Stock as determined by the Committee by the reasonable application of such reasonable valuation
method, consistently applied, as the Committee deems appropriate; <U>provided</U> <U>further</U>, <U>however</U>, that, with respect to ISOs, such Fair Market Value shall be determined subject to Section&nbsp;422(c)(7) of the Internal Revenue Code.
For purposes of the foregoing, a valuation prepared in accordance with any of the methods set forth in Treasury Regulation Section&nbsp;1.409A-1(b)(5)(iv)(B)(2), consistently used, shall be rebuttably presumed to result in a reasonable valuation.
This definition is intended to comply with the definition of &#147;fair market value&#148; contained in Treasury Regulation Section&nbsp;1.409A-1(b)(5)(iv) and should be interpreted consistently therewith. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><I>&#147;<U>Involuntary Termination</U>&#148;</I> means the termination of employment of the Participant by the Company or its successor for any reason on or after a
Change of Control; provided, that the termination does not result from an act of the Participant that (i)&nbsp;constitutes common-law fraud, a felony, or a gross malfeasance of duty, or (ii)&nbsp;is materially detrimental to the best interests of
the Company or its successor. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

hereof. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">(s)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><I><U>&#147;Participant&#148;</U></I> means an Eligible Person designated by the Committee, from time to time during the term of the Plan to receive one or more Awards
under the Plan. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">(t)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><I><U>&#147;Performance Award&#148;</U></I> is a right to either a number of shares of Stock or SARs (&#147;Performance Shares&#148;) determined (in either case) in
accordance with subsection&nbsp;9.1 of this Plan based on the extent to which the applicable Performance Goals are achieved. A Performance Share shall be of no value to a Participant unless and until earned in accordance with subsection 9.2 hereof.
</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">(u)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><I><U>&#147;Performance Goals&#148;</U></I> are the performance conditions, if any, established pursuant to subsection 9.1 by the Committee in connection with an Award.
</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">(v)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><I><U>&#147;Performance Period&#148;</U></I> with respect to a Performance Award is a period not less than one calendar year or one fiscal year of the Company,
beginning not earlier than the year in which such Performance Award is granted, which may be referred to herein and by the Committee by use of the calendar of fiscal year in which a particular Performance Period commences. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><I><U>&#147;Restricted Stock&#148;</U></I> means Stock granted to an Eligible Person under Section&nbsp;8 hereof, that is subject to certain restrictions and to a risk
of forfeiture. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

thereof at the end of a specified vesting period. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><I><U>&#147;Stock&#148;</U></I> means the $0.625 par value common stock of the Company and or any security into which such common stock is converted or exchanged upon
merger, consolidation, or any capital restructuring (within the meaning of Section&nbsp;13) of the Company. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><I><U>&#147;Stock Appreciation Right&#148;</U></I> or <I><U>&#147;SAR&#148;</U></I> means a right granted to an Eligible Person to receive an amount in cash, Stock, or
other property equal to the excess of the Fair Market Value as of the Exercise Date of one share of Stock over the SAR Price times the number of shares of Stock to which the Stock Appreciation Right relates. Stock Appreciation Rights may be granted
in tandem with Options or other Awards or may be freestanding. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><I><U>&#147;SAR Price&#148;</U></I> means the price at which the Stock Appreciation Right was granted, which shall be determined in the same manner as the Option Price
of an Option in accordance with subsection 6.2 hereof. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><I>&#147;<U>Voluntary Termination with Cause</U>&#148;</I> occurs upon a Participant&#146;s separation from service of his own volition and one or more of the following
conditions occurs without the Participant&#146;s consent on or after a Change of Control: </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">There is a material diminution in the Participant&#146;s base compensation, compared to his rate of base compensation on the date of the Change of Control.
</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">There is a material diminution in the Participant&#146;s authority, duties or responsibilities. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="10%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">(iii)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">There is a material diminution in the authority, duties or responsibilities of the Participant&#146;s supervisor, such as a requirement that the Participant (or his
supervisor) report to a corporate officer or employee instead of reporting directly to the board of directors. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="10%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">(iv)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">There is a material diminution in the budget over which the Participant retains authority. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="10%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">(v)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">There is a material change in the geographic location at which the Participant must perform his service, including, for example the assignment of the Participant to a
regular workplace that is more than 50 miles from his regular workplace on the date of the Change of Control. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">The Participant
must notify the Company of the existence of one or more adverse conditions specified in clauses (i)&nbsp;through (v)&nbsp;above within 90 days of the initial existence of the adverse condition. The notice must be provided in writing to Apache
Corporation&#146;s Senior Vice President, Human Resources or his/her delegate. The notice may be provided by personal delivery or it may be sent by email, inter-office mail, regular mail (whether or not certified), fax, or any similar method. Apache
Corporation&#146;s Senior Vice President, Human Resources or his/her delegate shall acknowledge receipt of the notice within 5 business days; the acknowledgement shall be sent to the Participant by certified mail. Notwithstanding the foregoing
provisions of this definition, if the Company remedies the adverse condition within 30 days of being notified of the adverse condition, no Voluntary Termination with Cause shall occur. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">2.2 <I><U>Headings; Gender and Number</U>.</I> The headings contained in the Plan are for reference purposes only and shall not affect in any way the meaning or interpretation of the Plan. Except when
otherwise indicated by the context, the masculine gender shall also include the feminine gender, and the definition of any term herein in the singular shall also include the plural. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">Section&nbsp;3 </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">Plan Administration </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">3.1
<I><U>Administration by the Committee.</U></I> The Plan shall be administered by the Committee. In accordance with the provisions of the Plan, the Committee shall, in its sole discretion, adopt rules and regulations for carrying out the purposes of
the Plan, including, without limitation, the authority to: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">3.2 <I><U>Committee Discretion</U></I>. The Committee shall, in its absolute discretion, and without amendment to the Plan, have the power to accelerate, waive or modify, at any time, any term or
condition of an Award that is not mandatory under this Plan; provided, however, that the Committee shall not have any discretion to accelerate, waive or modify any term or condition of an Award that is intended to qualify as &#147;performance-based
compensation&#148; for purposes of Section&nbsp;162(m) of the Internal Revenue Code if such discretion would cause the Award to not so qualify. In the event of a Change of Control, the provisions of Section&nbsp;12 hereof shall be mandatory and
shall govern the vesting and exercisability schedule of any Award granted hereunder. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">3.3 <I><U>Indemnification</U></I>. No member of the
Committee shall be liable for any action, omission, or determination made in good faith. The Company shall indemnify (to the extent permitted under Delaware law) and hold harmless each member of the Committee and each other director or employee of
the Company to whom any duty or power relating to the administration or interpretation of the Plan has been delegated against any cost or expense (including counsel fees) or liability (including any sum paid in settlement of a claim with the
approval of the Committee) arising out of any action, omission or determination relating to the Plan, unless, in either case, such action, omission or determination was taken or made by such member, director or employee in bad faith and without
reasonable belief that it was in the best interests of the Company. The determination, interpretations and other actions of the Committee pursuant to the provisions of the Plan shall be binding and conclusive for all purposes and on all persons.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">3.4 <I><U>Committee Delegation</U>.</I> </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">The Committee may from time to time adopt such rules and regulations for carrying out the purposes of the Plan as it may deem proper and in the best
interests of the </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>

Company. The Committee may appoint an Administrative Agent, who need not be a member of the Committee or an employee of the Company, to assist the Committee in administration of the Plan and to
whom it may delegate such powers as the Committee deems appropriate, except that the Committee shall determine any dispute. The Committee may correct any defect, supply any omission or reconcile any inconsistency in the Plan, or in any Award
agreement entered into hereunder, in the manner and to the extent it shall deem expedient, and it shall be the sole and final judge of such inconsistency; </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">(b)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">The Committee has delegated authority to the Chief Executive Officer of the Company to grant Awards to employees of the Company who are not the Company&#146;s executive
officers (as such term is defined for purposes of Section&nbsp;16 of the Exchange Act) and who are below the level of Regional Vice President or Staff Vice President; provided, that any such Awards may only be granted in accordance with guidelines
established by the Committee. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">3.5 <I><U>Compliance with Section&nbsp;162(m).</U></I> Except as expressly otherwise stated in any
resolution of the Committee, the Plan is intended to comply with the requirements of Section&nbsp;162(m) or any successor section(s) of the Internal Revenue Code (&#147;Section 162(m)&#148;) as to any &#147;covered employee&#148; as defined in
Section&nbsp;162(m), and shall be administered, interpreted, and construed consistently therewith. The Committee is authorized to take such additional action, if any, that may be required to ensure that the Plan and any Award under the Plan satisfy
the requirements of Section&nbsp;162(m), taking into account any regulations or other guidance issued by the Internal Revenue Service. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">Section&nbsp;4 </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">Stock Subject to the Plan </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">4.1 <I><U>Number of Shares</U></I>. Subject to adjustments pursuant to Section&nbsp;4.4 hereof, up to 25,500,000 shares of Stock are authorized for
issuance under the Plan in accordance with the Plan&#146;s terms and subject to such restrictions or other provisions as the Committee may from time to time deem necessary. Notwithstanding the foregoing, the number of aggregate shares of Stock
available for issuance under the Plan at any given time shall be reduced by (i)&nbsp;1.0 share for each share of Stock granted in the form of Stock Options or Stock Appreciation Rights, or (ii)&nbsp;2.39 shares for each share of Stock granted in the
form of any Award that is not a Stock Option or Stock Appreciation Right. During the duration of the Plan, no Eligible Person may be granted Options which in the aggregate cover in excess of 10 percent of the total shares of Stock authorized under
the Plan. No Award may be granted under the Plan on or after the 10-year anniversary of the Effective Date. The foregoing to the contrary notwithstanding, within the aggregate limit described in the first sentence of this Section&nbsp;4.1, up to
25,500,000 shares of Stock may be issued pursuant to ISOs granted under the Plan. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">4.2 <I><U>Availability of Shares Not Issued under
Awards</U>.</I> If shares of Stock which may be issued pursuant to the terms of the Plan awarded hereunder are forfeited, cancelled, exchanged or surrendered or if an Award otherwise terminates or expires without a distribution of shares to the
holder of such Award, the shares of Stock with respect to such Award shall, to the extent </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">B-7
</FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">
of any such forfeiture, cancellation, exchange, surrender, termination or expiration, again be available for Awards under the Plan; provided, however, that in such case, the number of shares of
Stock that may be issued under the Plan shall increase by 1.0 share for each share related to a Stock Option or a Stock Appreciation Right that is so forfeited, cancelled, exchanged or surrendered or expired and by 2.39 shares for each such share
which is not related to a Stock Option or a Stock Appreciation Right. The number of shares available shall not be increased by shares tendered, surrendered or withheld in connection with the exercise or settlement of an Award or the related tax
withholding obligations. Furthermore, when a SAR is settled in shares, the number of shares subject to the SAR under the SAR Award agreement will be counted against the aggregate number of shares with respect to which Awards may be granted under the
Plan as one share for every share subject to the SAR, regardless of the number of shares used to settle the SAR upon exercise. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">4.3 <I><U>Stock
Offered</U>.</I> The Company shall at all times during the term of the Plan retain as authorized and unissued Stock and/or Stock in the Company&#146;s treasury, at least the number of shares from time to time require under the provisions of the
Plan, or otherwise assure itself of its ability to perform its obligations hereunder. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">4.4 <I><U>Adjustments for Stock Split, Stock Dividend,
Etc</U>.</I> If the Company shall at any time increase or decrease the number of its outstanding shares of Stock or change in any way the rights and privileges of such shares by means of the payment of a Stock dividend or any other distribution upon
such shares payable in Stock or rights to acquire Stock, or through a Stock split, reverse Stock split, subdivision, consolidation, combination, reclassification or recapitalization involving the Stock (any of the foregoing being herein called a
&#147;capital restructuring&#148;), then in relation to the Stock that is affected by one or more of the above events, the numbers, rights, and privileges of the following shall be, in each case, equitably and proportionally adjusted to take into
account the occurrence of any of the above events, (i)&nbsp;the number and kind of shares of Stock or other property (including cash) that may thereafter be issued pursuant to subsections 4.1 and 4.10, (ii)&nbsp;the number and kind of shares of
Stock or other property (including cash) issued or issuable in respect of outstanding Awards; and (iii)&nbsp;the exercise price, grant price, or purchase price relating to any Award; provided that, with respect to Incentive Stock Options, such
adjustment shall be made in accordance with Section&nbsp;424(h) of the Internal Revenue Code; (iv)&nbsp;the Performance Goals, and (v)&nbsp;the individual limitations applicable to Awards. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">4.5 <I><U>Other Changes in Stock</U>.</I> In the event there shall be any change, other than as specified in subsections 4.4 hereof, in the number or kind of outstanding shares of Stock or of any stock or
other securities into which the Stock shall be changed or for which it shall have been exchanged, and if the Committee shall in its discretion determine that such change equitably requires an adjustment in the number or kind of shares subject to
outstanding Awards or which have been reserved for issuance pursuant to the Plan but are not then subject to an Award, then such adjustments shall be made by the Committee and shall be effective for all purposes of the Plan and on each outstanding
Award that involves the particular type of stock for which a change was effected. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">4.6 <I><U>Rights to Subscribe</U></I>. If the Company shall
at any time grant to the holders of its Stock rights to subscribe pro rata for additional shares thereof or for any other securities of the </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">B-8
</FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">
Company or of any other corporation, there shall be reserved with respect to the shares then under an outstanding Award to any Participant of the particular class of Stock involved the Stock or
other securities which the Participant would have been entitled to subscribe for if immediately prior to such grant the Participant had exercised his entire Option. If, upon exercise of any such Option, the Participant subscribes for the additional
shares or other securities, the aggregate Option Price shall be increased by the amount of the price that is payable by the Participant for such additional shares or other securities as if the Participant had exercised his entire Option immediately
prior to the grant of such additional shares or other securities. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">4.7 <I><U>General Adjustment Rules</U></I>. No adjustment or substitution
provided for in this Section&nbsp;4 shall require the Company to sell a fractional share of Stock under any Option, or otherwise issue a fractional share of Stock, and the total substitution or adjustment with respect to each Option shall be limited
by deleting any fractional share. In the case of any such substitution or adjustment, the aggregate Option Price for the shares of Stock then subject to the Option shall remain unchanged but the Option Price per share under each such Option shall be
equitably adjusted by the Committee to reflect the greater or lesser number of shares of Stock or other securities into which the Stock subject to the Option may have been changed. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">4.8 <I><U>Determination by the Committee, Etc</U>.</I> Adjustments under this Section&nbsp;4 shall be made by the Committee, whose determinations with regard thereto shall be final and binding upon all
parties. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">4.9 <I><U>Code Section&nbsp;409A</U></I>. For any Award that is not subject to Internal Revenue Code Section&nbsp;409A before the
adjustments identified in the preceding sections of this Section&nbsp;4, no adjustment shall be made that would cause the Award to become subject to Internal Revenue Code Section&nbsp;409A. For an Award that is subject to Internal Revenue Code
Section&nbsp;409A before the adjustments identified in the preceding sections of this Section&nbsp;4, no adjustment shall cause the Award to violate Internal Revenue Code Section&nbsp;409A, without the prior written consent of both the Participant
and the Committee. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">4.10 <I><U>Award Limits</U></I>. The following limits shall apply to grants of all Awards under the Plan: </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><I><U>Options</U></I>: The maximum aggregate number of shares of Stock that may be subject to Options granted in any calendar year to any one Participant shall be
250,000 shares. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><I><U>SARs</U>:</I> The maximum aggregate number of shares that may be subject to Stock Appreciation Rights granted in any calendar year to any one Participant shall be
250,000 shares. Any shares covered by Options which include tandem SARs granted to one Participant in any calendar year shall reduce this limit on the number of shares subject to SARs that can be granted to such Participant in such calendar year.

shares (or SARs based on the value of such number of shares). </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">B-9

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">To the extent required by Section&nbsp;162(m) of the Code, shares subject to Options or SARs which are
canceled shall continue to be counted against the limits set forth in paragraphs&nbsp;(a) and (b)&nbsp;immediately preceding. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">4.11
<I><U>Repayment/Forfeiture of Awards</U></I>. If required by the Sarbanes-Oxley Act of 2002 and/or by the Dodd-Frank Wall Street Reform and Consumer Protection Act of 2010, each Participant&#146;s Award shall be conditioned on repayment or
forfeiture in accordance with applicable law and the related Award agreement shall reflect any such condition. In addition, the Committee may establish such conditions for repayment or forfeiture of Awards as the Committee may adopt by policy for
the Company or any Affiliate. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">Section&nbsp;5 </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">Granting of Awards to Participants </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">5.1 <I><U>Participation.</U></I> Participants in the Plan
shall be those Eligible Persons who, in the judgment of the Committee (or, pursuant to Section&nbsp;3.4(b), the Chief Executive Officer of the Company), are performing, or during the term of their incentive arrangement will perform, vital services
in the management, operation, and development of the Company or an Affiliate, and significantly contribute, or are expected to significantly contribute, to the achievement of the Company&#146;s long-term corporate economic objectives. Participants
may be granted from time to time one or more Awards; provided, however, that the grant of each such Award shall be separately approved by the Committee or granted in accordance with Section&nbsp;3.4(b) hereof, and receipt of one such Award shall not
result in automatic receipt of any other Award. Upon determination that an Award is to be granted to a Participant, as soon as practicable, written notice shall be given to such person, specifying the terms, conditions, rights and duties related
thereto. Each Participant shall, if required by the Committee, enter into an agreement with the Company, in such form as the Committee shall determine and which is consistent with the provisions of the Plan, specifying such terms, conditions,
rights, and duties. Awards shall be deemed to be granted as of the date specified in the grant resolution of the Committee (or, in the case of grants made pursuant to Section&nbsp;3.4(b), in accordance with the guidelines established by the
Committee), which date shall be the date of any related agreement with the Participant. In the event of any inconsistency between the provisions of the Plan and any such agreement entered into hereunder, the provisions of the Plan shall govern.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">Awards granted to members of the Board shall be recommended to the full Board by the Management Development and Compensation Committee and
approved by the full Board. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">5.2 <I><U>Notification to Participants and Delivery of Documents</U>.</I> As soon as practicable after such
determinations have been made, each Participant shall be notified of (a)&nbsp;his/her designation as a Participant, (b)&nbsp;the date of grant, (c)&nbsp;the number and type of Awards granted to the Participant, (d)&nbsp;in the case of Performance
Awards, the Performance Period and Performance Goals, (e)&nbsp;in the case of Restricted Stock or Restricted Stock Units, the Restriction Period (as defined in subsection 8.1), and (f)&nbsp;any other terms or conditions imposed by the Committee with
respect to the Award. </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">B-10
</FONT></P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">5.3 <I><U>Delivery of Award Agreement</U></I>. This requirement for delivery of a written Award agreement is
satisfied by electronic delivery of such agreement provided that evidence of the Participant&#146;s receipt of such electronic delivery is available to the Company and such delivery is not prohibited by applicable laws and regulations. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">Section&nbsp;6 </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">Stock Options </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">6.1 <I><U>Grant
of Stock Options</U></I>. Coincident with or following designation for participation in the Plan, an Eligible Person may be granted one or more Options. Grants of Options under the Plan shall be made by the Committee or in accordance with
Section&nbsp;3.4(b). In no event shall the exercise of one Option affect the right to exercise any other Option or affect the number of shares of Stock for which any other Option may be exercised, except as provided in subsection 6.2(j) hereof.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">6.2 <I><U>Stock Option Agreements</U></I>. Each Option granted under the Plan shall be identified as either an Incentive Stock Option or a
Non-Qualified Stock Option (or, if no such identification is made, then it shall be a Non-Qualified Stock Option) and evidenced by a written agreement which shall be entered into by the Company and the Participant to whom the Option is granted, and
which shall contain the following terms and conditions set out in this subsection&nbsp;6.2, as well as such other terms and conditions, not inconsistent therewith, as the Committee may consider appropriate. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">(a)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><I><U>Number of Shares</U></I>. Each Stock Option agreement shall state that it covers a specified number of shares of Stock, as determined by the Committee.
</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">(b)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><I><U>Price.</U></I> The price at which each share of Stock covered by an Option may be purchased, the Option Price, shall be determined in each case by the Committee
and set forth in the Stock Option agreement. The price may vary according to a formula specified in the Stock Option agreement, but in no event shall the Option Price ever be less than the Fair Market Value of the Stock on the date the Option is
granted. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">(c)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><I><U>No Backdating</U></I>. There shall be no backdating of Options, and each Option shall be dated the actual date that the Committee adopts the resolution awarding
the grant of such Option. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">(d)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><I><U>Limitations on Incentive Stock Options</U></I>. No Incentive Stock Option may be granted to an individual if, at the time of the proposed grant, such individual
owns (or is attributed to own by virtue of the Internal Revenue Code) Stock possessing more than 10 percent of the total combined voting power of all classes of stock of the Company or any Affiliate unless (i)&nbsp;the exercise price of such
Incentive Stock Option is at least 110 percent of the Fair Market Value of a share of Stock at the time such Incentive Stock Option is granted and (ii)&nbsp;such Incentive Stock Option is not exercisable after the expiration of five years from the
date such Incentive Stock Option is granted. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">To the extent that the aggregate Fair Market Value of Stock of the Company with
respect to which Incentive Stock Options are exercisable for the first time by a Participant during any calendar year under the Plan and any other option plan of the Company (or any Affiliate) shall
</FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">B-11
</FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">
exceed $100,000, such Options shall be treated as Non-Qualified Stock Options. Such Fair Market Value shall be determined as of the date on which each such Incentive Stock Option is granted.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">(e)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><I><U>Duration of Options</U></I>. Each Stock Option agreement shall state the period of time, determined by the Committee, within which the Option may be exercised by
the Participant (the &#147;Option Period&#148;). The Option Period must end, in all cases, not more than ten years from the date an Option is granted. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">(f)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><I><U>Termination of Options</U></I>. During the lifetime of a Participant to whom a Stock Option is granted, the Stock Option may be exercised only by such Participant
or, in the case of disability (as determined pursuant to the Company&#146;s Long-Term Disability Plan or any successor plan) by the Participant&#146;s designated legal representative, except to the extent such exercise would cause any Award intended
to qualify as an ISO not to so qualify. Once a Participant to whom a Stock Option was granted dies, the Stock Option may be exercised only by the personal representative of the Participant&#146;s estate or, with respect to Stock Options that are not
Incentive Stock Options, as otherwise provided in Section&nbsp;14.2. Unless the Stock Option agreement shall specify a longer or shorter period, at the discretion of the Committee, then the Participant (or representative, or, if applicable pursuant
to Section&nbsp;14.2, designated beneficiary) may exercise the Stock Option for a period of up to three months after such Participant terminates employment or ceases to be a member of the Board. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">(g)</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><I><U>Exercise, Payments, Etc</U></I>. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:10%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">(i) Each Stock Option agreement shall provide that the method for exercising the Option granted therein shall be by delivery to the Office of the Secretary of the Company or to the Administrative Agent of
written notice specifying the number of shares of Stock with respect to which such Option is exercised and payment to the Company of the aggregate Option Price. Such notice shall be in a form satisfactory to the Committee and shall specify the
particular Options (or portions thereof) which are being exercised and the number of shares of Stock with respect to which the Options are being exercised. The Participant&#146;s obligation to deliver written notice of exercise is satisfied by
electronic delivery of such notice through means satisfactory to the Committee and prescribed by the Company. The exercise of the Option shall be deemed effective on the date such notice is received by the Office of the Secretary or by the
Administrative Agent and payment is made to the Company of the aggregate Option Price (the &#147;Exercise Date&#148;); however, if payment of the aggregate Option Price is made pursuant to a sale of shares of Stock as contemplated by subsection
6.2(g)(iv)(E) below, the Exercise Date shall be deemed to be the date of such sale. If requested by the Company, such notice shall contain the Participant&#146;s representation that he or she is purchasing the Stock for investment purposes only and
his or her agreement not to sell any Stock so purchased in any manner that is in violation of the Exchange Act or any applicable state law, and such restriction, or notice thereof, shall be placed on the certificates representing the Stock so
purchased. The purchase of such Stock shall take place upon delivery of such notice to the Office of the Secretary of the Company or to the Administrative </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">B-12
</FONT></P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:10%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">
Agent, at which time the aggregate Option Price shall be paid in full to the Company by any of the methods or any combination of the methods set forth in subsection&nbsp;6.2(g)(iv) below.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:10%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">(ii) The shares of Stock to which the Participant is entitled as a result of the exercise of the Option shall be issued by
the Company and either (A)&nbsp;delivered by electronic means to an account designated by the Participant or (B)&nbsp;delivered to the Participant in the form of a properly executed certificate or certificates representing such shares of Stock. If
shares of Stock are used to pay all or part of the aggregate Option Price, the Company shall issue and deliver to the Participant the additional shares of Stock, in excess of the aggregate Option Price or portion thereof paid using shares of Stock,
to which the Participant is entitled as a result of the Option exercise. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:10%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">(iii) The Company&#146;s obligation to deliver the
shares of Stock to which the Participant is entitled as a result of the exercise of the Option shall be subject to the payment in full to the Company of the aggregate Option Price and the required tax withholding. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:10%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3">(iv) The aggregate Option Price shall be paid by any of the following methods or any combination of the following methods: </FONT></P>

Value of which (as of the Exercise Date) is equal to the aggregate Option Price of the Option being exercised, properly endorsed for transfer to the Company, provided that the shares of Stock used for this purpose must have been owned by the
Participant for a period of at least six months; </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

the aggregate Fair Market Value of which (as of the Exercise Date) is not greater than the aggregate Option Price of the Option being exercised, provided that the shares of Stock used for this purpose have been owned by the Participant for a period
of at least six months; or </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
